# TypeScript

- Use strict TypeScript configuration - strict mode enabled, no implicit any
- Always type function parameters and return types - no implicit any
- Use interfaces for object shapes, types for unions/intersections
- Match Rust types from src/core/types.rs exactly - MessageId, AgentId, Role, AgentState, CanonicalMessage
- Use readonly for immutable data structures
- Prefer const assertions for literal types
- Use discriminated unions for type-safe state management
- Never use `any` - use `unknown` and type guards if needed
- Export types from dedicated types/ directory - keep types organized
